{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637010","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637010"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:36:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:36:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17622"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17622","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17622"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10336"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71676"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10336"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17622"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57172"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7752"},{"type":"tags","id":"7753"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24182"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24187"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71676","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71676"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA researcher wants to investigate whether a new study technique improves examination scores compared to traditional methods. They need to formulate appropriate hypotheses before conducting their statistical analysis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the null hypothesis for this study?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["There is no difference in examination scores between the new and traditional study methods","The new study technique increases examination scores compared to traditional methods","The relationship between study technique and examination scores is unknown","The new study technique reduces examination scores compared to traditional methods","The new study method will have different examination scores than traditional methods"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Enull hypothesis states there is no difference in examination scores between the new and traditional study methods\u003C/strong\u003E. This is the default position that must be disproven with statistical evidence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe new study technique increases examination scores compared to traditional methods\u003C/strong\u003E - This is an alternative hypothesis, not a null hypothesis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe new study technique reduces examination scores compared to traditional methods\u003C/strong\u003E - This is another possible alternative hypothesis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe new study method will have different examination scores than traditional methods\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a non-directional alternative hypothesis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe relationship between study technique and examination scores is unknown\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a statement of uncertainty, not a testable hypothesis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The null hypothesis (H0) states there is no effect, difference, or relationship between variables.","The alternative hypothesis (H1) states there is an effect, difference, or relationship between variables.","Statistical tests aim to either reject or fail to reject the null hypothesis based on evidence."],"references":[